I am building an AI-powered educational platform called "Mathlers" for my organization. We have been operating for 10 years with a physical curriculum that teaches mathematics through real-world records and game-based "cards." Now we want to digitalize everything. I need your detailed assistance in designing an AI model that can:

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CORE OBJECTIVE:
Build an AI/Math Model that automatically generates endless, unique math questions using REAL-WORLD DATA (current records, stats, achievements from 2026), replacing our manual card-based system. This model should power a digital competition platform where students practice and compete in a "boxing ring / punch box" themed environment.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

BACKGROUND CONTEXT (Our Organization):
• Name: Mathlers
• Mission: Introduce mathematics as a game — like a boxing ring or punch box where students of different ages come to learn math
• Method: We use real-world records from different games/sports to create math "portions" (lessons/problems)
• History: 10 years ago we built a physical book/curriculum using cards with world records to engage young students in mathematics
• Current Goal: Digitalize the entire process — from content creation to student competition

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WHAT THE AI MODEL MUST DO:

1. DATA INGESTION & MANAGEMENT
   • Continuously collect and update real-world records from 2026+ sources (sports, esports, gaming, science, entertainment, etc.)
   • Structure data into "Record Cards" with fields: record title, holder, numeric value, unit, previous record, date, category, location, source, difficulty tags, age range
   • Maintain data freshness — auto-update when new records are broken

2. QUESTION GENERATION ENGINE
   • Generate unlimited unique math questions using the real numbers from Record Cards
   • Support multiple math topics: arithmetic, percentages, ratios, algebra, geometry, probability, statistics, time/speed, money/finance
   • Support difficulty levels: Easy (ages 8-10), Medium (11-13), Hard (14-16), Expert (16+)
   • Each question should be framed as a "boxing round" with engaging narrative
   • Include: scenario setup, main question, multiple choice options, correct answer, step-by-step solution, and a "Knockout Round" bonus challenge
   • Ensure mathematical accuracy — validate all generated answers

3. COMPETITION & TEST AUTOMATION
   • Auto-generate complete tests/competitions with themed "matches"
   • Each match = multiple rounds (Warm-up → Jab → Hook → Uppercut → Knockout)
   • Adaptive difficulty: adjust based on student performance
   • Time limits per round, scoring system with speed bonuses and streak multipliers
   • Generate leaderboards, rankings, and "Champion Belts" for top performers

4. PERSONALIZATION & ENGAGEMENT
   • Adapt questions to student age, skill level, and interests (favorite games/sports)
   • Track progress and recommend practice areas
   • Generate daily challenges, weekly tournaments, and special events

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

THE DIGITAL "PUNCH BOX" COMPETITION PLATFORM:

The platform should include:
• Practice Mode (solo vs AI, any difficulty)
• Sparring (1v1 friendly matches)
• Ranked Matches (ELO-based matchmaking)
• Tournaments (weekly/monthly championships)
• School/Organization leaderboards
• Global rankings by age group and topic

Gamification elements:
• Boxing ring metaphor: rounds, knockouts, comebacks
• "Champion Belts" for weekly winners
• Streak bonuses for consecutive correct answers
• "Comeback Kid" reward for recovering after wrong answers
• Topic mastery badges

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

REAL-WORLD DATA SOURCES TO INTEGRATE:
• Guinness World Records
• Esports Charts (viewership, prize pools)
• Esports World Cup / Tournament data
• Speedrun.com (gaming records)
• Traditional sports APIs (ESPN, Sports Reference)
• Steam/player count APIs
• Gaming achievements (Xbox, PlayStation, Steam)
• Scientific records (space, technology, nature)
• Entertainment records (box office, music streaming)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

